Root Cause

 In beads-kanban/src/lib/wsStore.svelte.ts, the sendToPane function (lines 318-340) has flawed logic:

 Problem: When a session exists but streaming is false (after completion), it sends type: 'start' creating a NEW session instead of sending type: 'message' to continue the existing one.

 // Lines 327-334 - THIS IS THE BUG
 } else if (!session.streaming) {
   send({
     type: 'start',  // Should be 'message' type instead
     ...
   });
 }

 Flow:
 1. First message → no session → sends start → server creates session
 2. Agent finishes → streaming: false
 3. Second message → session exists but streaming is false → sends start again → server creates NEW session

 Fix

 The client should send type: 'message' for follow-ups regardless of whether the previous response finished. A completed response (streaming: false) doesn't mean the session is dead - it just means the agent is waiting for the next user
 input.

